\begin_layout Subsubsection
Conservation Laws
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Most of the nonlinear PDEs coming from physics can be formulated as conservation
s laws, i.e.
 the law of conservation of some physical quatity (mass, momentum, angular
 momentum, energy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Suppose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $V^{C}$
\end_inset

 is a 
\noun on
control volume
\noun default
 in space.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $\partial V^{C}$
\end_inset

 is the boundary of 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

, which is moving with a velocity 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{u}^{C}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 is the 
\noun on
density
\noun default
 of some physical quantity, i.e.
 something per unit volume.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{u}$
\end_inset

 is the velocity of a fluid particle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{f}:=\phi\vec{u}$
\end_inset

 is the 
\noun on
flux
\noun default
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

, i.e.
 how much 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 pass through a 
\emph on
fixed
\emph default
 surface per unit area in unit time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, the 
\noun on
conservation law
\noun default
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 can be written as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\boxed{\MDV{}{t}\int_{V^{C}}\phi\dd{V}=\int_{V^{C}}\pdv{\phi}{t}\dd{V}+\oint_{\partial V^{C}}\vec{f}\cdot\vu{n}\dd{S}=0}
\]

\end_inset

which is usually used for fixed control volumes, or
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\boxed{\MDV{}{t}\int_{V^{C}}\phi\dd{V}=\dv{t}\int_{V^{C}}\phi\dd{V}+\oint_{\partial V^{C}}\left(\vec{f}-\phi\vec{u}^{C}\right)\cdot\vu{n}\dd{S}}
\]

\end_inset

which is usually used for moving control volumes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{f}$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $C^{1}$
\end_inset

 smooth with respect to spatial variables, we can apply Gauss's divergence
 theorem, which leads to
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\boxed{\pdv{\phi}{t}+\div\vec{f}=0}
\]

\end_inset

However, if the 
\begin_inset Formula $C^{1}$
\end_inset

 smooth prerequisite is not satisfied, we should go back to the integral
 form.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Discontinuity Condition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Suppose there is a discontinuity surface 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 moving with velocity 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\vec{u}^{S}=\vu{e}_{\perp}u_{\perp}^{S}+\vu{e}_{\parallel}u_{\parallel}^{S}
\]

\end_inset

Choose a cylindrical control volume 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{C}$
\end_inset

, which satisfies the following requirements:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
It has an infinitesimal height 
\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

.
 When 
\begin_inset Formula $h\to0$
\end_inset

, formulas can be simplified, since
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lim_{h\to0}\vec{u}^{C}=\vec{u}^{S}\qc\lim_{h\to0}\dv{t}\int_{V^{C}}\phi\dd{V}=0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
All of its walls are 
\begin_inset Formula $\perp S$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is sandwiched between the top 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{+}$
\end_inset

 (on which 
\begin_inset Formula $\vu{n}=\vu{e}_{\perp}$
\end_inset

) and the bottom 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{-}$
\end_inset

 (on which 
\begin_inset Formula $\vu{n}=-\vu{e}_{\perp}$
\end_inset

) of 
\begin_inset Formula $V^{C}$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{+}\parallel S\parallel S_{-}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, the conservation law is reduced to
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lim_{h\to0}\oint_{\partial V}\left(\vec{f}-\phi\vec{u}^{S}\right)\cdot\vu{n}\dd{S}=\int_{S_{+}\cup S_{-}}\left(\vec{f}-\phi\vec{u}^{S}\right)\cdot\vu{n}\dd{S}
\]

\end_inset

Replace 
\begin_inset Formula $\vu{n}$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $\pm\vu{e}_{\perp}$
\end_inset

 and let 
\begin_inset Formula $\int_{S_{\pm}}\dd{S}\to0$
\end_inset

, we have
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\boxed{u_{\perp}^{S}=\frac{f_{+}-f_{-}}{\phi_{+}-\phi_{-}}\qc f_{\pm}=\lim_{h\to\pm0}\vec{f}\cdot\vu{e}_{\perp}}
\]

\end_inset

which is called the 
\noun on
jump condition
\noun default
 aka the 
\noun on
Rankineâ€“Hugoniot condition
\noun default
.
\end_layout

